cs.DL, cs.CR, cs.IR, cs.SE, cs.DB 

This paper discusses the field of digital preservation, which involves managing and preserving digital information over the long term. The most relevant sub-category is cs.DL (Digital Libraries), which focuses on the management and preservation of digital content. The paper also discusses security threats and system requirements, which could place it in the cs.CR (Cryptography and Security) and cs.IR (Information Retrieval) sub-categories. Additionally, the paper discusses the development and certification of digital preservation systems, which could place it in the cs.SE (Software Engineering) sub-category. Finally, the paper discusses the importance of data management and storage, which could place it in the cs.DB (Databases) sub-category.
